Builder Comparison with ProtoType
&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&&

Prototype: It uses Object cloning. It clones the existing Object and return the object. 



@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@
Usage of Constructor
@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@
Builder  : We will have a complex constructor and the builder allows us to work with that 
constructor.

Prototype: Prototype allows altogether skip using constructor. 
Whoever is going to create the  prototype the design pattern will be calling the 
clone method to create the object.




@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@
When used with legacy code
@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@

Builder  : We can create a seperate class and so that it can allow to work with legacy code.
 
Prototype: In java this pattern works using clone method and needs to modify existing code 
so that it may work with legacy code.
In this particular example we work by over-writing the clone method in object class.
So with prototype design pattern it might not always be possible or feasible to work
with legacy code 





